OL,5, Changing how children are measured for 
OL,6, obesity to a new system could be more  
OL,7, accurate, a study has concluded.       
OL,9,FIt revealed the traditional method of  
OL,10,Fusing Body Mass Index (BMI) is not as  
OL,11,Fuseful in measuring fat as             
OL,12,Fwaist-to-height ratio (WHtR).          
OL,14,FOver a 15-year follow-up, 7,237        
OL,15,Fnine-year-old children were studied.   
OL,17,FThe findings could change guidelines   
OL,18,Fthat recommend BMI as a measure.       
OL,19,FResearchers said it was critical to    
OL,20,Faccurately detects obesity in children.
